A '''biopsy''' is a test in [[medicine]] where [[Medical doctor|doctors]] remove [[cell]]s and look at them closely under a [[microscope]] or do [[chemical]] analysis to see whether there is an [[illness]].

== Etymology ==

Biopsy is a Greek word, from the Greek words '''bio''' meaning "life" and '''opsia''' meaning see.


